s in an Unequal America offers an up-to-the-moment assessment of the condition of the family in an era of growing inequality. Highlighting unique aspects of family behavior, it reveals the degree to which families' varying experiences are shaped by social class. This book offers a much needed assessment of contemporary family life amid the turbulent economic changes in the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aEqualityzUnited States. 0aFamilieszUnited States. 0aSocial classeszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Marriage & Family.2bisacsh1 aCarlson, Marcia J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEngland, Paula, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477908140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804779081423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804779081.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles